**********************************************************************
      Prerequisites
**********************************************************************

You need GNU gcc, GNU binutils and qemu. All three are free software
and readily available for most platforms.

You need a PC compatible machine. We have not tested the build process
on e.g. the Macintosh.



**********************************************************************
    Installation instructions
**********************************************************************

Step 1.

Run 
     su
     make

or
     sudo make

Step 2.

Wait (it's just a few seconds on my machine).


Step 3.

Run
        ./run

Step 4.

You should see a qemu window pop up, with a GRUB boot menu in which
you can select OS 134. There's not much to see yet, but it (kinda)
works.
